# agent-stack

My personal AI agent configuration repo. Contains all agent definitions, skills, hooks, and stack configurations for agentic coding in Cursor.

Shared across projects via git submodule. Improve a prompt once — every project gets it.

---

## What's Inside
```
agent-stack/
├── core/                          # Tech-agnostic agents (work for any project)
│   ├── agents/
│   │   ├── requirements-agent.md  # Produces Given/When/Then acceptance criteria
│   │   ├── planner-agent.md       # Breaks features into ordered atomic tasks
│   │   ├── ticket-writer-agent.md # Enriches tasks into full ticket documents
│   │   ├── test-definer-agent.md  # Defines unit vs e2e split and coverage goals
│   │   ├── mutation-tester-agent.md # Reads Stryker report, flags test gaps
│   │   └── reviewer-agent.md      # Final cross-layer sign-off
│   └── skills/
│       ├── atomic-commits.md      # Conventional commits, one concern per commit
│       ├── ticket-format.md       # Standard ticket structure all agents follow
│       └── tdd-flow.md            # Red → green → refactor discipline
│   ├── rules/
│   │   └── intent-routing.mdc    # Classify requests → full feature / continue / quick fix / review
│   └── hooks/
│       ├── cursor/               # Cursor hooks (event-driven)
│       │   ├── event-logger.js   # Logs all hook events to ~/.cursor/hooks-logs/
│       │   ├── block-dangerous-commands.js  # PreToolUse: blocks rm -rf ~, curl|sh, etc.
│       │   └── post-tool-use-check.js       # PostToolUse: eslint + tsc after file write
│       └── git/                  # Git hooks (copied to .git/hooks/ on setup)
│           └── commit-msg-append-review.sh    # Appends .cursor/review-append.txt to commit body
│
├── stacks/                        # Tech-specific agent bundles
│   ├── react-hono-trpc/           # React + Hono + tRPC + Drizzle + Supabase + Better Auth
│   │   ├── agents/
│   │   │   ├── db-agent.md        # Drizzle schema + Supabase migrations
│   │   │   ├── storage-agent.md   # Supabase Storage buckets + RLS policies
│   │   │   ├── api-agent.md       # Hono routes + tRPC routers
│   │   │   ├── auth-agent.md      # Better Auth wiring + session typing
│   │   │   ├── ui-design-agent.md # Component tree, layout, states
│   │   │   ├── ui-agent.md        # React + Shadcn implementation
│   │   │   ├── unit-test-writer-agent.md # Failing Vitest specs
│   │   │   ├── e2e-test-writer-agent.md  # Failing Playwright specs
│   │   │   └── e2e-runner-agent.md       # Runs + self-heals Playwright tests
│   │   └── skills/
│   │       ├── agent-registry.md   # Agents + layers (planner loads this)
│   │       ├── trpc-patterns.md
│   │       ├── shadcn-conventions.md
│   │       ├── better-auth-rules.md
│   │       ├── drizzle-schema.md
│   │       ├── supabase-storage.md
│   │       └── typescript-strict.md
│   │
│   └── electron/                  # Electron overrides on top of react-hono-trpc
│       ├── agents/
│       │   └── ui-agent.md        # Overrides base ui-agent (no Shadcn, native UI)
│       └── skills/
│           └── electron-ipc.md
│
└── commands/
    └── commit.md                  # /commit slash command definition
```

---

## Agent Pipeline
```
requirements-agent → ticket-writer-agent → planner-agent → test-definer-agent
                                                                        ↓
                                    unit-test-writer + e2e-test-writer  ← failing specs first
                                                                        ↓
                              db → storage → api → auth → ui   ← each atomic commit
                                                                        ↓
                                    e2e-runner → mutation-tester → reviewer  ← mutation testing is a plan task, not a git hook
                                                                        ↓
                                    commit (hook appends review to message)
```

---

## Setting Up in a New Project

### 1. Add as a submodule
```bash
git submodule add git@github.com:you/agent-stack.git .cursor/shared
git submodule update --init
```

### 2. Symlink into Cursor's expected paths
```bash
# Core — always loaded in every project
ln -s .cursor/shared/core/agents   .cursor/agents/core
ln -s .cursor/shared/core/skills   .cursor/skills/core

# Stack — pick your stack
ln -s .cursor/shared/stacks/react-hono-trpc/agents  .cursor/agents/stack
ln -s .cursor/shared/stacks/react-hono-trpc/skills  .cursor/skills/stack

# Rules (intent classification for routing)
ln -s .cursor/shared/core/rules  .cursor/rules/core

# Hooks (Cursor event hooks + Git hooks)
ln -s .cursor/shared/core/hooks  .cursor/hooks
ln -s .cursor/shared/commands    .cursor/commands

# Git commit-msg hook (appends review snippet to commit body)
cp .cursor/shared/core/hooks/git/commit-msg-append-review.sh .git/hooks/commit-msg
chmod +x .git/hooks/commit-msg
```

For an Electron project, add the override layer on top:
```bash
ln -s .cursor/shared/stacks/electron/agents  .cursor/agents/electron
ln -s .cursor/shared/stacks/electron/skills  .cursor/skills/electron
```

### 3. Create your project AGENT.md
```bash
touch .cursor/AGENT.md
```

Minimal content:
```markdown
## Stack
react-hono-trpc

## Layers loaded
- .cursor/agents/core
- .cursor/agents/stack

## Project-specific notes
- DB: Supabase (self-hosted)
- Auth: Better Auth with session strategy
- No overrides — all shared agents apply as-is
```

### 4. Configure MCP servers

Create `.cursor/mcp.json` in your project:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "supabase": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "-y",
        "@supabase/mcp-server-supabase@latest",
        "--supabase-url", "https://your-project.supabase.co",
        "--supabase-key", "${SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY}",
        "--features", "database,storage"
      ]
    },
    "playwright": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@playwright/mcp@latest"]
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Keeping Projects Up to Date

When you improve an agent or skill in this repo:
```bash
# In agent-stack
git commit -m "refactor: improve ticket-writer prompt"
git push

# In any project using it
git submodule update --remote --merge
```

Add this alias to your shell to make it a one-liner:
```bash
# .zshrc or .bashrc
alias ai-sync="git submodule update --remote --merge"
```

Then syncing any project is just:
```bash
ai-sync
```

---

## Override Priority

When Cursor loads agents and skills, project-level files always win:
```
1. .cursor/agents/          ← project-specific, highest priority
2. .cursor/agents/electron  ← electron stack override (if loaded)
3. .cursor/agents/stack     ← base stack (react-hono-trpc)
4. .cursor/agents/core      ← tech-agnostic baseline
```

---

## Versioning

Tag stable states of the repo so projects can pin to a known-good version:
```bash
git tag -a v1.0.0 -m "stable: react-hono-trpc stack complete"
git push --tags
```

Pin a project to a specific version:
```bash
cd your-project
git -C .cursor/shared checkout v1.0.0
```
